                <note rend="inline" type="source">793.94/3103: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in China</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Johnson</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Peiping</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1931-12-08T14:00:00+08:00"
                            >December 8, 1931—2 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received December 8—9:20 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>1056. Following from Margetts, Chinchow: <quote rend="blockquote">
                        <p>“December 7, 6 p.m. Statement of observers, including American Military
                            Attaché from Tokyo. Have spent the entire day personally checking units
                            of Nineteenth, Twentieth Brigades and Thirteenth Artillery Regiment
                            reported by Mukden Japanese headquarters to be Faku. In some instances
                            we counted the soldiers, finding absolutely no discrepancies. Entire
                            Twentieth Brigade is in immediate vicinity Chinchow. Referring to repair
                            railway, Yingkow, statement of same was made by Chinese laborers under
                            the supervision two British railway engineers and during presence one of
                            our observers who returned late yesterday afternoon.”</p>
                    </quote>
                </p>
                <p>Repeated to Department and Nanking.</p>
                <closer>For the Minister:<lb/>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Perkins</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
